---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="EVA · Voice AI for Elderly Users" description="EVA is a voice-first AI companion designed for elderly users. The problem isn't ability; it's that technology isn't designed for them.">
  <div class="bg-slate-950 min-h-screen">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <a href="/projects" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">← All projects</a>

    <div class="mb-2">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium text-amber-400 bg-amber-950/50 rounded px-2.5 py-1">Building</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-2">EVA</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 mb-10">Voice-first AI companion for elderly users.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          "The problem isn't their ability. The problem is that technology isn't designed for them."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Elderly users are systematically excluded from modern technology. Not because of lack of ability, but because technology isn't designed for them. Smartphones are too complex. Interfaces rely on habits they've never built. Voice assistants are tuned for speed, not patience. I saw this first-hand, and I couldn't leave it alone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The solution</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">One interaction model: press a button, speak. That's it. From there, EVA handles the rest.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            "Reminders and calendar management via natural voice",
            "Answers questions in plain, patient language",
            "Initiates and manages calls",
            "Provides daily context ('what do I have tomorrow?')",
            "No apps, no screens, no learning curve",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▸</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What makes this hard</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          The technical complexity is manageable. The real challenge is trust. Latency matters enormously: a 3-second pause is confusion, not patience. Every added feature is a potential failure point. One wrong answer can end the relationship. The product isn't functionality, it's confidence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Where we are</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Product vision, system architecture and MVP scope defined. Currently in user validation: testing whether real elderly users understand it, want it, and actually use it before committing to full development. Real evidence first. Code second.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Key learnings</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          {[
            "Voice latency is the #1 UX variable: sub-1s response is non-negotiable",
            "Simplicity isn't a design choice — it's the entire product strategy",
            "Trust is fragile and asymmetric. Easy to break, slow to rebuild",
            "Designing for elderly users requires rethinking every assumption about usability",
            "Validation in real environments beats any amount of desk research",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-slate-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0">·</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {["Voice AI", "Healthcare", "Python", "LLM", "UX Research"].map(tag => (
        <span class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-950/40 rounded px-2 py-0.5">{tag}</span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
